# SAIL Helm — environment template
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values for local dev.
# `.env` is gitignored (covered by `.env*` in sail-platform-shell/.gitignore).
#
# IMPORTANT: do not commit real keys to this repository. Vite inlines
# `VITE_*` env values at build time — they ship in the client bundle.
# Anything else stays server-side. Both Helm builds (dev + prod) must
# rebuild after changing values here.
#
# Phase B4 (2026-05-08) — proxy-only architecture:
# Helm calls `ai-proxy` (Supabase Edge Function) directly via supabase-js.
# There is NO local Netlify Function. There is NO fallback. There is NO
# flag. The only AI-related secret in the entire system is OPENAI_API_KEY,
# and it lives ONLY on the Edge Function (Supabase Dashboard → Edge
# Functions → ai-proxy → Settings → Secrets).

# ─── Optional client-side (VITE_* — bundled into browser code) ──────────────
#
# Deployment-mode tag, surfaced into ai_requests metadata via
# pages/Assignments.jsx so per-deploy traffic is filterable in DB.
# Set to a stable identifier per environment: dev / staging / prod.
# VITE_DEPLOYMENT_MODE=dev
